Dalton Massey is a professional rodeo contestant who has made a name for himself in the world of steer wrestling. Born and raised in a family with a strong rodeo background, Massey has been involved in the sport since a young age. With a career marked by impressive achievements, including breaking records and winning prestigious events, Massey has become a prominent figure in the rodeo community.

Here you can follow Dalton Massey’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Dalton Massey

Dalton Massey was born into a family with deep roots in rodeo. His grandfather was a bareback rider, and his grandmother ran barrels, while his father was a steer wrestler and his mother and wife both competed in barrel racing.

This strong family connection to the sport has undoubtedly played a significant role in shaping Massey’s passion for rodeo and his determination to succeed.

Growing up, Massey was inspired by his family’s dedication to the sport and their achievements in the rodeo arena. 

This early exposure to the world of rodeo helped to instill in him a strong work ethic and a desire to excel in the sport, which has served him well throughout his career.

Early Career

Dalton Massey’s early career in rodeo began with modest success. In his rookie season in 2014, he participated in 19 rodeos throughout the Pacific Northwest and earned just $1,388.

Despite these humble beginnings, Massey remained determined to improve and continued to work hard, both in and out of the arena.

Professional Career

Dalton Massey is a professional rodeo contestant specializing in steer wrestling. He began his career in 2014, competing in 19 rodeos throughout the Pacific Northwest and earning $1,388 in his rookie season.

Over the years, Massey has steadily climbed the ranks, breaking records and achieving significant milestones in his career.

In 2023, Massey had a standout season, leading the World Standings for almost the entire year. He won several major rodeos, including RodeoHouston, where he earned $54,250. By the end of the regular season, Massey had earned over $193,000, further extending his record.

Dalton Massey’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Dalton Massey’s net worth is estimated to be $1 million.

Career Earnings

Dalton Massey’s career earnings have seen a significant increase since his rookie season in 2014, when he earned just $1,388.

Over the next four years, he steadily climbed the ranks, earning a total of $24,340. However, it was in 2023 that Massey’s earnings skyrocketed

Major wins in 2023 contributed significantly to Massey’s earnings. For instance, he won $54,250 at RodeoHouston, $15,931 at the Washington State Fair Rodeo, and $18,062 at the Ponoka Stampede in Alberta, Canada.

As of November 2023, Massey’s career earnings stand at $216,820.

Personal Details

Wife

Dalton Massey is married to Hilary Massey (née Imhof). Both Dalton and Hilary share a passion for rodeo, with Hilary being a barrel racer.

Their shared love for the sport has played a significant role in Dalton’s success and determination to excel in the rodeo arena. The couple got married in the fall of 2022.

How Old is Dalton Massey?

He is 30 years old.

What is his nationality?

He is an American.
